INSERT INTO `kvblobstore` VALUES ('3c594662-f580-4f78-86bf-fe505db1fd0b','json-arr','{\"title\":\"FreePBX \\u2013 Let Freedom Ring\",\"description\":\"Let Freedom Ring\",\"items\":[{\"title\":\"FreePBX 17 Beta and  the Future with Debian\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/freepbx-17-beta-release-and-debian-future\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>A little over a month ago now, the FreePBX Engineering team had published a wiki page with instructions for manually setting up FreePBX 17 on Debian Linux using the beta release tarball. The wiki migration project (which you can read about here) delayed the Beta announcement for FreePBX 17 a bit, but here we are [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/freepbx-17-beta-release-and-debian-future\\/\\\">FreePBX 17 Beta and  the Future with Debian<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"Introducing CDR Pro: A Powerful Call Reporting Enhancer Module\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/introducing-cdr-pro-call-reporting-module\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>CDR Pro is a new commercial module for FreePBX and PBXact systems that simplifies the call reporting experience for administrators by providing an intuitive interface for generating detailed call reports. CDR Pro allows you to present straightforward lists of inbound calls to a specific DID for a particular date range and to set up automated [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/introducing-cdr-pro-call-reporting-module\\/\\\">Introducing CDR Pro: A Powerful Call Reporting Enhancer Module<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"Open Source Projects at Sangoma\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/open-source-projects-at-sangoma\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>This is a cross-post on both the Asterisk and the FreePBX blogs, so for those who may only be familiar with FreePBX let me introduce myself. My name is Joshua Colp. I\\u2019m the Project Lead for the Asterisk project, the telephony toolkit that powers FreePBX. For those on the Asterisk side, Hi again! Over the [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/open-source-projects-at-sangoma\\/\\\">Open Source Projects at Sangoma<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"Sangoma Completing the Open Source Move to GitHub\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/freepbx-is-moving-to-github\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>TL;DR \\u2013 Effective immediately, Sangoma is migrating the Atlassian stack that is currently hosting issues.freepbx.org and git.freepbx.org to GitHub. Hello everyone, happy Friday. As has been announced previously, and has been already done successfully for the Asterisk project earlier this year, FreePBX is migrating away from the Atlassian stack in use for project issues and [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/freepbx-is-moving-to-github\\/\\\">Sangoma Completing the Open Source Move to GitHub<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"The FreePBX Wiki is Moving!\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/the-freepbx-wiki-is-moving\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>Hello All, TL;DR \\u2013 FreeBPX\\/PBXact wiki content has moved to https:\\/\\/help.sangoma.com Similarly to what was recently done for the Asterisk project, the FreePBX project has had a plan in place for some time now to move many of the public facing resources to a new home. Part one of this move is the subject of [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/the-freepbx-wiki-is-moving\\/\\\">The FreePBX Wiki is Moving!<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"FreePBX 