e. Over the past few weeks, the new Mirror infrastructure has been operating flawlessly, and we are extremely pleased with [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/freepbx-mirror-infrastructure\\/\\\">FreePBX Mirror Infrastructure<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"Brand New Module \\u2013 Missed Call Notification\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/missed-call-notification-new-module\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>For the first time in a while, the FreePBX Engineering team has published a new Open Source module, the Missed Call Notification module. This module satisfies the request that comes up periodically in the FreePBX Community Forum to have the PBX generate a notification whenever a call to an extension goes unanswered. With this module, [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/missed-call-notification-new-module\\/\\\">Brand New Module \\u2013 Missed Call Notification<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"},{\"title\":\"PBX MFA \\u2013 New FreePBX Commercial Module Release\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/mfa-new-freepbx-module-authentication\\/\",\"content\":\"<p>Hello Everyone! We are pleased to announce the launch of a new commercial module named \\u201cPBX MFA\\u201d to the FreePBX ecosystem. It is targeted towards FreePBX and PBXact version 16 and above, but it can also be used by systems running version 15. What is MFA? Multi-factor Authentication (MFA) is an authentication method that requires [\\u2026]<\\/p>\\n<p>The post <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/mfa-new-freepbx-module-authentication\\/\\\">PBX MFA \\u2013 New FreePBX Commercial Module Release<\\/a> appeared first on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.freepbx.org\\/\\\">FreePBX - Let Freedom Ring<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"}]}'),('3f40b203-291a-4f68-bf3d-440b6f00549e','json